#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing multipath I/O for devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes how to manage failover and path load balancing for "
"multiple paths between the servers and block storage devices by using "
"Multipath I/O (MPIO)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "Understanding multipath I/O"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipathing is the ability of a server to communicate with the same "
"physical or logical block storage device across multiple physical paths "
"between the host bus adapters in the server and the storage controllers for "
"the device, typically in Fibre Channel (FC) or iSCSI SAN environments."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Linux multipathing provides connection fault tolerance and can provide load "
"balancing across the active connections. When multipathing is configured and "
"running, it automatically isolates and identifies device connection "
"failures, and reroutes I/O to alternate connections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipathing provides fault tolerance against connection failures, but not "
"against failures of the storage device itself. The latter is achieved with "
"complementary techniques like mirroring."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Storage array\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t A hardware device with many disks and multiple\t fabrics connections "
"(controllers) that provides SAN or NAS storage\t to clients. Storage arrays "
"typically have RAID and failover\t features and support multipathing. "
"Historically,\t active/passive (failover) and active/active\t (load-"
"balancing) storage array configurations were\t distinguished. These concepts "
"still exist but they are merely\t special cases of the concepts of path "
"groups and access\t states supported by modern hardware.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Host, host system\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The computer running &productname; which acts as a client system\t for a "
"<emphasis>storage array</emphasis> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Multipath map, multipath device\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t A set of <emphasis>path devices</emphasis> . It represents a\t storage "
"volume on a storage array and is seen as\t a single block device by the host "
"system.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Path device\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t A member of a multipath map, typically a SCSI device.\t Each path device "
"represents a unique\t connection between the host computer and the actual "
"storage\t volume, for example, a logical unit from an iSCSI session.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t WWID\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t &ldquo;World Wide Identifier&rdquo;. <systemitem>multipath-tools</"
"systemitem> \t uses the WWID to\t determine which low-level devices should "
"be assembled into a\t multipath map.\t The WWID must be distinguished from "
"the configurable <emphasis>map\t name</emphasis> (see\t <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-names\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t uevent, udev event\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t An event sent by the kernel to user space and processed by the\t "
"<command>udev</command> subsystem. Uevents are generated when\t devices are "
"added, removed, or change their properties.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Device mapper\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t A framework in the Linux kernel for creating virtual block\t devices. I/O "
"operations to mapped devices are redirected to\t the underlying block "
"devices. Device mappings may be\t stacked. The device mapper implements its "
"own event signaling,\t also known as &ldquo;device mapper events&rdquo;\t or "
"&ldquo;dm events&rdquo;.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t initramfs\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The initial RAM file system, also referred to as\t &ldquo;initial RAM "
"disk&rdquo; (initrd)\t for historical reasons (see <xref linkend=\"sec-boot-"
"terminology\"/> ).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t ALUA\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t &ldquo;Asymmetric Logical Unit Access&rdquo;, a concept introduced\t with "
"the SCSI standard SCSI-3. Storage volumes can be accessed via\t multiple "
"ports, which are organized in port groups with different\t states (active, "
"standby, etc.). ALUA defines SCSI commands to\t query the port groups and "
"their states, and change the state\t of a port group. Modern storage arrays "
"that support SCSI usually\t support ALUA, too.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hardware support"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The multipathing drivers and tools are available on all architectures "
"supported by &productname;. The generic, protocol-agnostic driver works with "
"most multipath-capable storage hardware on the market. Some storage array "
"vendors provide their own multipathing management tools. Consult the "
"vendor’s hardware documentation to determine what settings are required."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath implementations: device mapper and NVMe"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The traditional, generic implementation of multipathing under Linux uses the "
"device mapper framework. For most device types like SCSI devices, device "
"mapper multipathing is the only available implementation. Device mapper "
"multipath is highly configurable and flexible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Linux <emphasis>NVM Express</emphasis> (NVMe) kernel subsystem "
"implements multipathing natively in the kernel. This implementation creates "
"less computational overhead for NVMe devices, which are typically fast "
"devices with very low latencies. Native NVMe multipathing requires no user "
"space component. Since &slea; 15, native multipathing has been the default "
"for NVMe multipath devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter documents device mapper multipath and its user-space component, "
"<systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> . <systemitem>multipath-tools</"
"systemitem> also has limited support for native NVMe multipathing (see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-misc\" xrefstyle=\"SecTitleOnPage\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage array autodetection for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Device mapper multipath is a generic technology. Multipath device detection "
"requires only that the low-level (for example, SCSI) devices are detected by "
"the kernel, and that device properties reliably identify multiple low-level "
"devices as being different &ldquo;paths&rdquo; to the same volume rather "
"than actually different devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>multipath-tools</filename> package detects storage arrays by "
"their vendor and product names. It has validated built-in configuration "
"defaults for a large variety of storage products. Consult the hardware "
"documentation of your storage array: some vendors provide specific "
"recommendations for Linux multipathing configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to apply changes to the built-in configuration for your storage "
"array, read <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-file\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disclaimer about built-in hardware properties"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>multipath-tools</filename> has built-in presets for many storage "
"arrays. The existence of such presets for a given storage product "
"<emphasis>does not imply</emphasis> that the vendor of the storage product "
"has tested the product with <systemitem>dm-multipath</systemitem> , nor that "
"the vendor endorses or supports use of <systemitem>dm-multipath</systemitem> "
"with the product. Always consult the original vendor documentation for "
"support-related questions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage arrays that require specific hardware handlers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some storage arrays require special commands for failover from one path to "
"the other, or non-standard error handling methods. These special commands "
"and methods are implemented by hardware handlers in the Linux kernel. Modern "
"SCSI storage arrays support the &ldquo;Asymmetric Logical Unit Access&rdquo; "
"(ALUA) hardware handler defined in the SCSI standard. Besides ALUA, the "
"&slea; kernel contains hardware handlers for Netapp E-Series (RDAC), the "
"Dell/EMC CLARiiON CX family of arrays, and legacy arrays from HP."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since Linux kernel 4.4, the Linux kernel has automatically detected hardware "
"handlers for most arrays, including all arrays supporting ALUA. The only "
"requirement is that the device handler modules are loaded at the time the "
"respective devices are probed. The <systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> "
"package ensures this by installing appropriate configuration files. Once a "
"device handler is attached to a given device, it cannot be changed any more."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Planning for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the guidelines in this section when planning your multipath I/O solution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The storage array you use for the multipathed device must support "
"multipathing. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-"
"hardware\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to configure multipathing only if multiple physical paths exist "
"between host bus adapters in the server and host bus controllers for the "
"block storage device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For some storage arrays, the vendor provides its own multipathing software "
"to manage multipathing for the array’s physical and logical devices. In this "
"case, you should follow the vendor’s instructions for configuring "
"multipathing for those devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using multipathing in a virtualization environment, the multipathing is "
"controlled in the host server environment. Configure multipathing for the "
"device before you assign it to a virtual guest machine."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath installation types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We distinguish installation types by the way the root device is handled. "
"<xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-installing\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> "
"describes how the different setups are created during and after installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "Root file system on multipath (SAN-boot)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tThe root file system is on a multipath device.\tThis is typically the case "
"for\tdiskless servers that use SAN or NAS storage exclusively. On such"
"\tsystems, multipath support is required for booting, and multipathing\tmust "
"be enabled in the initramfs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Root file system on a local disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tThe root file system (and possibly some other file systems) is on local"
"\tstorage, for example, on a directly attached SATA disk or local RAID,\tbut "
"the system additionally uses file systems in the multipath SAN or NAS"
"\tstorage. This system type can be configured in three different ways:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:346
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath setup for local disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t All block devices are part of multipath maps, including the local disk.\t "
"The root device appears as a degraded multipath map with just one\t path. "
"This configuration is created if multipathing was enabled during\t the "
"initial system installation with &yast;.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local disk blacklisted"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t In this configuration, multipathing is enabled in the initramfs,\t but "
"the root device is blacklisted (see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist"
"\"/> ).\t <xref linkend=\"pr-multipath-disable-root\"/> describes how to set"
"\t up this configuration.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath disabled in the initramfs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t This setup is created if multipathing was not enabled during\t the "
"initial system installation with &yast;.\t This configuration is rather "
"fragile; consider using one of the other\t options instead.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:382
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk management tasks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use third-party SAN array management tools or the user interface of your "
"storage array to create logical devices and assign them to hosts. Make sure "
"to configure the host credentials correctly on both sides."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add or remove volumes to a running host, but detecting the changes "
"may require rescanning SCSI targets and reconfiguring multipathing on the "
"host. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-best-practice-scandev\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage processors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On some disk arrays, the storage array manages the traffic through storage "
"processors. One processor is active and the other one is passive until there "
"is a failure. If you are connected to the passive storage processor, you "
"might not see the expected LUNs, or you might see the LUNs but encounter I/O "
"errors when you try to access them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a disk array has more than one storage processor, ensure that the SAN "
"switch has a connection to the active storage processor that owns the LUNs "
"you want to access."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:412
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software RAID and complex storage stacks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipathing is set up on top of basic storage devices such as SCSI disks. "
"In a multi-layered storage stack, multipathing is always the bottom layer. "
"Other layers such as software RAID, Logical Volume Management, block device "
"encryption, etc. are layered on top of it. Therefore, for each device that "
"has multiple I/O paths and that you plan to use in a software RAID, you must "
"configure the device for multipathing before you attempt to create the "
"software RAID device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "High-availability solutions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"High-availability solutions for clustering storage resources run on top of "
"the multipathing service on each node. Make sure that the configuration "
"settings in the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file on each node "
"are consistent across the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that multipath devices have the same name across all devices. "
"Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-names\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Distributed Replicated Block Device (DRBD) high-availability solution "
"for mirroring devices across a LAN runs on top of multipathing. For each "
"device that has multiple I/O paths and that you plan to use in a DRDB "
"solution, you must configure the device for multipathing before you "
"configure DRBD."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Special care must be taken when using multipathing together with clustering "
"software that relies on shared storage for fencing, such as "
"<command>pacemaker</command> with <command>sbd</command> . See <xref linkend="
"\"sec-multipath-policies-cluster\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:456
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing &productname; on multipath systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No special installation parameters are required for installation of "
"&productname; on systems with multipath hardware."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing without connected multipath devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may want to perform a normal installation on a local disk, without "
"configuring the fabric and the storage first, with the intention to add "
"multipath SAN devices to the system later on. In this case, the installation "
"will proceed like on a non-multipath system. After installation, "
"<systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> will be installed, but the systemd "
"service <filename>multipathd.service</filename> will be disabled. The system "
"will be configured as described in <xref linkend=\"vl-multipath-planning-"
"type-noroot-noinitrd\"/> in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-planning-type-"
"noroot\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> . Before adding SAN hardware, you "
"will need to enable and start <filename>multipathd.service</filename> . It "
"is recommended to create a blacklist entry for the root device (see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing with connected multipath devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multipath devices are connected to the system at installation time, "
"&yast; will detect this and display a pop-up window asking the user whether "
"multipath should be enabled before entering the partitioning stage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: textobject
#: storage_multipath.xml:490
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase> &yast; multipath dialog</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:501
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the user selects &ldquo;No&rdquo; at this prompt (not recommended), "
"installation will proceed as in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-installing-nomp"
"\"/> . In the partitioning stage, you should <emphasis>avoid touching "
"devices</emphasis> that will later be part of a multipath map."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:508
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the user selects &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; at the multipath prompt, "
"<command>multipathd</command> will run during installation. No blacklist "
"will be configured, thus all SCSI and DASD devices, including local disks, "
"will appear as multipath devices in the partitioning dialogs. After "
"installation, all SCSI and DASD devices will be multipath devices, as "
"described in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-planning-type-root\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:519
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling multipathing for the root disk after installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tThis procedure assumes that you installed on a local disk,\tand enabled "
"multipathing during\tinstallation, so that the root device is on multipath "
"now.\tBut you prefer to set up the system as described in\t <xref linkend="
"\"vl-multipath-planning-type-noroot-ignore\"/> \tin <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-planning-type-noroot\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Check your system for <filename>/dev/mapper/...</filename> \t references "
"to your local root device, and replace them with references\t that will "
"still work if the device is not a multipath map any more\t (see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec-multipath-referring\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ). If "
"the following command finds no\t references, you do not need to apply "
"changes:\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:538
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;grep -rl /dev/mapper/ /etc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Switch to <literal>by-uuid</literal> persistent device policy for\t "
"<command>dracut</command> \t (see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-"
"persistent\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ):\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:547
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;echo 'persistent_policy=\"by-uuid\"' | \\\n"
"      sudo tee /etc/dracut.conf.d/10-persistent-policy.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:551
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Determine the WWID of the root device:\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;multipathd show paths format \"%i %d %w %s\"\n"
"0:2:0:0 sda 3600605b009e7ed501f0e45370aaeb77f IBM,ServeRAID M5210\n"
"...\n"
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t This command prints all paths devices with their WWIDs and vendor/product"
"\t information. You will be able to identify the root device\t (here, the "
"ServeRAID device) and note the WWID.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Create a blacklist entry in <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> \t "
"(see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/"
"> )\t with the WWID you just determined (do <emphasis>not</emphasis> \t "
"apply these settings just yet):\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"    wwid 3600605b009e7ed501f0e45370aaeb77f\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Rebuild the initramfs:\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:582
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Reboot. Your system should boot with a non-multipath root disk now.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:589
#, no-c-format
msgid "Offline Update on multipath systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The offline update system behaves exactly as described for the installation "
"system above. There is no blacklist, thus if the user selects to enable "
"multipath, the root device will appear as a multipath device, even if it is "
"normally not. When <command>dracut</command> builds the initramfs during the "
"update procedure, it sees a different storage stack as it would see on the "
"booted system. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-persistent\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> and <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-referring"
"\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath management tools"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The multipathing support in &productname; is based on the Device Mapper "
"Multipath module of the Linux kernel and the <systemitem>multipath-tools</"
"systemitem> user space package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:615
#, no-c-format
msgid "Device mapper multipath module"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Device Mapper Multipath (DM-MP) module <filename>dm-multipath.ko</"
"filename> provides the generic multipathing capability for Linux. DM-MPIO is "
"the preferred solution for multipathing on &productname; for SCSI and DASD "
"devices, and can be used for NVMe devices as well."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:625
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using DM-MP for NVMe devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &productname; 15, native NVMe multipathing (see <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-hardware-implementations\"/> ) has been recommended for NVMe and "
"used by default. To disable native NVMe multipathing and use device mapper "
"multipath instead ( <emphasis>not recommended</emphasis> ), boot with the "
"kernel parameter <literal>nvme-core.multipath=0</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Device Mapper Multipath module handles the following tasks:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:641
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Distributing load over multiple paths inside the active path group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Noticing I/O errors on path devices, and marking these as\t failed, so "
"that no I/O will be sent to them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:652
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Switching path groups when all paths in the active path group have\t "
"failed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:658
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Either failing or queuing I/O on the multipath device if all paths\t have "
"failed, depending on configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Device Mapper Multipath module does <emphasis role=\"bold\">not</"
"emphasis> handle the following tasks:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Discovering devices representing different paths to\t the same storage "
"device, and assembling multipath maps from them,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:675
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Collecting path devices with similar properties into path groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Monitoring path devices actively for failure or reinstantiation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Monitoring of addition and removal of path devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The Device Mapper Multipath module does not provide an easy-to-use user "
"interface for setup and configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above-mentioned tasks are handled by the user space components in the "
"<systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> package. See <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-mpiotools-multipathd\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:701
#, no-c-format
msgid "Failures that multipath prevents"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DM-MPIO protects against failures in the paths to the device, and not "
"failures in the device itself, such as media errors. The latter kind of "
"errors must be prevented by other means, such as replication."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath I/O management tools"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The packages <systemitem class=\"resource\">multipath-tools</systemitem> and "
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">kpartx</systemitem> provide tools that take "
"care of automatic path discovery and grouping."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:721
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t <command>multipathd</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:725
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The daemon to set up and monitor multipath maps, and a command line\t "
"client to communicate with the daemon process. See\t <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-mpiotools-multipathd\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:733
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t <command>multipath</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The command line tool for multipath operations. See\t <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-mpiotools-multipath\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:744
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t <command>kpartx</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The command line tool for managing &ldquo;partitions&rdquo; on multipath"
"\t devices. See\t <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-configuration-partitioning\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t <command>mpathpersist</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:760
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The command line tool for managing SCSI persistent reservations. See \t "
"<xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-mpiotools-mpathpersist\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:770
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:778
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>multipathd</command> daemon"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:779
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> is the most important part of a modern Linux "
"device mapper multipath setup. It is normally started through the systemd "
"service <filename>multipathd.service</filename> (see <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-configuration-start\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> serves the following tasks (some of them "
"depend on the configuration):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t On startup, detects path devices and sets up multipath maps from\t "
"detected devices.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Monitors uevents and device mapper events, adding or removing path\t "
"mappings to multipath maps as necessary and initiating failover or\t "
"failback operations.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:804
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Sets up new maps on the fly when new path devices are discovered.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Checks path devices at regular intervals to detect failure, and\t tests "
"failed paths to reinstate them if they become operational\t again.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:816
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t When all paths fail, <command>multipathd</command> either fails the map, "
"or switches the map\t device to queuing mode for a given time interval.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Handles path state changes and switches path groups or regroups\t paths, "
"as necessary.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:828
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Tests paths for &ldquo;marginal&rdquo; state, i.e. shaky fabrics\t "
"conditions that cause path state flipping between operational and\t non-"
"operational.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:835
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Handles SCSI persistent reservation keys for path devices \t if "
"configured. See\t <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-mpiotools-mpathpersist\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:843
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>multipathd</command> also serves as a command line client to "
"process interactive commands by sending them to the running daemon. The "
"general syntax to send commands to the daemon is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:848
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;multipathd <replaceable>COMMAND</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:849
#, no-c-format
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:852
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;multipathd -k'<replaceable>COMMAND</replaceable>'"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also an interactive mode that allows sending multiple subsequent "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:857
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;multipathd -k"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:859
#, no-c-format
msgid "How multipath and multipathd work together"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Many <command>multipathd</command> commands have\t <command>multipath</"
"command> equivalents. For example,\t <command>multipathd show topology</"
"command> does the same\t thing as <command>multipath -ll</command> . The "
"notable difference is\t that the multipathd command inquires the internal "
"state of the running\t <command>multipathd</command> daemon, whereas "
"multipath obtains\t information directly from the kernel and I/O operations."
"\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:869
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t If the multipath daemon is running, it is recommended to make\t "
"modifications to the system by using the\t <command>multipathd</command> "
"commands. Otherwise, the daemon may\t notice configuration changes and react "
"to them. In some situations,\t the daemon might even try to undo the applied "
"changes.\t <command>multipath</command> \t automatically delegates certain "
"possibly dangerous commands, like\t destroying and flushing maps, to "
"<command>multipathd</command> if\t a running daemon is detected.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:881
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The list bellow describes frequently used <command>multipathd</command> "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:884
#, no-c-format
msgid "show topology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:886
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tShows the current map topology and properties. See <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-best-practice-status\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:893
#, no-c-format
msgid "show paths"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:895
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the currently known path devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "show paths format \" <replaceable>FORMAT STRING</replaceable> \""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tShows the currently known path devices using a format string. Use\t "
"<command>show wildcards</command> to see a list of supported format "
"specifiers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid "show maps"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:912
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the currently configured map devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:918
#, no-c-format
msgid "show maps format <replaceable>FORMAT STRING</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tShows the currently configured map devices using a format string. Use\t "
"<command>show wildcards</command> to see a list of supported format "
"specifiers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:927
#, no-c-format
msgid "show config local"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:929
#, no-c-format
msgid "\tShows the current configuration that multipathd is using."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:935
#, no-c-format
msgid "reconfigure"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tReread configuration files, rescan devices, and set up maps\tagain. This "
"is basically equivalent to a restart of\t <command>multipathd</command> . A "
"few options cannot be modified\twithout a restart. They are mentioned in the "
"man page\t <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> . The\t "
"<option>reconfigure</option> command reloads only map devices that\thave "
"changed in some way. To force reloading every map device, use\t "
"<command>reconfigure all</command> (available since &sles;&nbsp;15\tSP4; on "
"previous versions, <option>reconfigure</option> \treloaded every map)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:952
#, no-c-format
msgid "del map <replaceable>MAP DEVICE NAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:954
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigure and delete the given map device and its partitions.\t "
"<replaceable>MAP DEVICE NAME</replaceable> can be a device node name like\t "
"<filename>dm-0</filename> , a WWID, or a map name. The command fails if\tthe "
"device is in use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:963
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"switchgroup map <replaceable>MAP DEVICE NAME</replaceable> group "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSwitch to the path group with the given numeric index (starting at 1)."
"\tThis is useful for maps with manual failback\t(see <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-policies-default\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additional commands are available to modify path states, enable or disable "
"queueing, and more. See <systemitem>multipathd(8)</systemitem> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:980
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>multipath</command> command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:981
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even though multipath setup is mostly automatic and handled by "
"<command>multipathd</command> , <command>multipath</command> is still useful "
"for some administration tasks. Several examples of the command usage follow:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:989
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:991
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detects path devices and configures all multipath maps that it finds."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:997
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -d"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:999
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSimilar to <command>multipath</command> , but does not set up\tany maps "
"(&ldquo;dry run&rdquo;)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1006
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configures a specific multipath device. <replaceable>DEVICENAME</"
"replaceable> can denote a member path device by its device node name "
"( <filename>/dev/sdb</filename> ) or device number in <literal>major:minor</"
"literal> format. Alternatively, it can be the WWID or name of a multipath "
"map."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1018
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -f <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1020
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigures (\"flushes\") a multipath map and its partition mappings."
"\tThe command will fail if the map or one of its partitions is in use.\tSee "
"above for possible values of <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1028
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -F"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1030
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tUnconfigures (\"flushes\") all multipath maps and their partition mappings."
"\tThe command will fail for maps in use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1037
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1039
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tDisplays the status and topology of all currently configured multipath"
"\tdevices. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-best-practice-status\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -ll <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1049
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Displays the status of a specified multipath device. See above for possible "
"values of <replaceable>DEVICENAME</replaceable> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1056
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1058
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows the internal hardware table and the active configuration of multipath. "
"Refer to <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> for details about the "
"configuration parameters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1067
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -T"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1069
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tHas a similar function as the <command>multipath -t</command> command\tbut "
"shows only hardware entries matching the hardware detected on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1076
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The option <option>-v</option> controls the verbosity of the output. It "
"overrides the <option>verbosity</option> option in <filename>/etc/multipath."
"conf</filename> . See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-misc\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1085
#, no-c-format
msgid "SCSI persistent reservations and <command>mpathpersist</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1086
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>mpathpersist</command> utility is used to manage SCSI "
"persistent reservations on Device Mapper Multipath devices. Persistent "
"reservations serve to restrict access to SCSI Logical Units to certain SCSI "
"initiators. In multipath configurations, it is important to use the same "
"reservation keys for all I_T nexuses (paths) for a given volume; otherwise, "
"creating a reservation on one path device would cause I/O errors on other "
"paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this utility with the <literal>reservation_key</literal> attribute in "
"the <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file to set persistent "
"reservations for SCSI devices. If (and only if) this option is set, the "
"<command>multipathd</command> daemon checks persistent reservations for "
"newly discovered paths or reinstated paths."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add the attribute to the <literal>defaults</literal> section or the "
"<literal>multipaths</literal> section of <filename>multipath.conf</"
"filename> . For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"multipaths {\n"
"    multipath {\n"
"        wwid             3600140508dbcf02acb448188d73ec97d\n"
"        alias            yellow\n"
"        reservation_key  0x123abc\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After setting <literal>reservation_key</literal> parameter for all mpath "
"devices applicable for persistent management, reload the configuration using "
"<command>multipathd reconfigure</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1120
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &ldquo; <option>reservation_key file</option> &rdquo;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the special value <literal>reservation_key file</literal> is used in the "
"<literal>defaults</literal> section of <filename>multipath.conf</filename> , "
"reservation keys can be managed dynamically in the file <filename>/etc/"
"multipath/prkeys</filename> using <command>mpathpersist</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the recommended way to handle persistent reservations with multipath "
"maps. It is available from &productname; 12 SP4."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the command <command>mpathpersist</command> to query and set persistent "
"reservations for multipath maps consisting of SCSI devices. Refer to the "
"manual page <systemitem>mpathpersist(8)</systemitem> for details. The "
"command line options are the same as those of the <command>sg_persist</"
"command> from the <systemitem>sg3_utils</systemitem> package. The "
"<systemitem>sg_persist(8)</systemitem> manual page explains the semantics of "
"the options in detail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the following examples, <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable> denotes a "
"device mapper multipath device like <filename>/dev/mapper/mpatha</"
"filename> . The commands below are listed with long options for better "
"readability. All options have single-letter replacements, like in "
"<command>mpathpersist -oGS 123abc <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable></"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1156
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist --in --read-keys <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Read the registered reservation keys for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1164
#, no-c-format
msgid "mpathpersist --in --read-reservation <replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show existing reservations for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --register --param-sark=123abc <replaceable>DEVICE</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Register a reservation key for the device. This will add the reservation key "
"for all I_T nexuses (path devices) on the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --reserve --param-rk=123abc --prout-type=5 "
"<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a reservation of type 5 (&ldquo;write exclusive - registrants "
"only&rdquo;) for the device, using the previously registered key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --release --param-rk=123abc --prout-type=5 "
"<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Release a reservation of type 5 for the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mpathpersist --out --register-ignore --param-sark=0 <replaceable>DEVICE</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1201
#, no-c-format
msgid "\t Delete a previously existing reservation key from the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the system for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling, starting, and stopping multipath services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable multipath services to start at boot time, run the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1220
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl enable multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1221
#, no-c-format
msgid "To manually start the service in the running system, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1224
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl start multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1225
#, no-c-format
msgid "To restart the service, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1228
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl restart multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In most situations, restarting the service is not necessary. To simply have "
"<command>multipathd</command> reload its configuration, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1233
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl reload multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1234
#, no-c-format
msgid "To check the status of the service, enter:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1237
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl status multipathd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid "To stop the multipath services in the current session, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl stop multipathd multipathd.socket\n"
"   "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stopping the service does not remove existing multipath maps. To remove "
"unused maps, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1248
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;multipath -F"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep <filename>multipathd.service</filename> enabled"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is strongly recommended to keep <filename>multipathd.service</filename> "
"always enabled and running on systems with multipath hardware. The service "
"does support <command>systemd</command> 's socket activation mechanism, but "
"it is discouraged to rely on that. Multipath maps will not be set up during "
"boot if the service is disabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to disable multipath despite the warning above, for example "
"because a third-party multipathing software is going to be deployed, proceed "
"as follows. Be sure that the the system uses no hard-coded references to "
"multipath devices (see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-trouble-ref\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable multipathing <emphasis>just for a single system boot</emphasis> , "
"use the kernel parameter <literal>multipath=off</literal> . This affects "
"both the booted system and the initramfs, which does not need to be rebuilt "
"in this case."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable multipathd services <emphasis>permanently</emphasis> , so that "
"they will not be started on future system boots, run the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;systemctl disable multipathd multipathd.socket\n"
"&prompt.sudo;dracut --force --omit multipath\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(Whenever you disable or enable the multipath services, rebuild the "
"<systemitem>initrd</systemitem> . See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-"
"sync\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> .)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to make sure multipath devices do not get set up, <emphasis>even "
"when running <command>multipath</command> manually</emphasis> , add the "
"following lines at the end of <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> "
"before rebuilding the initrd:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"blacklist {\n"
"    wwid .*\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1302
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing SAN devices for multipathing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before configuring multipath I/O for your SAN devices, prepare the SAN "
"devices, as necessary, by doing the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure and zone the SAN with the vendor’s tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure permissions for host LUNs on the storage arrays with the vendor’s "
"tools."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &productname; ships no driver for the host bus adapter (HBA), install a "
"Linux driver from the HBA vendor. See the vendor’s specific instructions for "
"more details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multipath devices are detected and <filename>multipathd.service</"
"filename> is enabled, multipath maps should be created automatically. If "
"this does not happen, <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-trouble-steps\" "
"xrefstyle=\"SecTitleOnPage\"/> lists some shell commands commands that can "
"be used to examine the situation. When the LUNs are not seen by the HBA "
"driver, check the zoning setup in the SAN. In particular, check whether LUN "
"masking is active and whether the LUNs are correctly assigned to the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the HBA driver can see LUNs, but no corresponding block devices are "
"created, additional kernel parameters may be needed. See <citetitle>TID "
"3955167: Troubleshooting SCSI (LUN) Scanning Issues</citetitle> in the "
"&suse; Knowledgebase at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/support/kb/"
"doc.php?id=3955167\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1347
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partitions on multipath devices and <command>kpartx</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multipath maps can have partitions like their path devices. Partition table "
"scanning and device node creation for partitions is done in user space by "
"the <command>kpartx</command> tool. <command>kpartx</command> is "
"automatically invoked by udev rules; there is usually no need to run it "
"manually. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-referring\"/> for ways to refer "
"to multipath partitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1358
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling invocation of <command>kpartx</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tThe <literal>skip_kpartx</literal> option in\t <filename>/etc/multipath."
"conf</filename> can be used to disable\tinvocation of <command>kpartx</"
"command> on selected multipath maps. This\tmay be useful on virtualization "
"hosts, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Partition tables and partitions on multipath devices can be manipulated as "
"usual, using &yast; or tools like <command>fdisk</command> or "
"<command>parted</command> . Changes applied to the partition table will be "
"noted by the system when the partitioning tool exits. If this does not work "
"(usually because a device is busy), try <command>multipathd reconfigure</"
"command> , or reboot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keeping the initramfs synchronized"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tMake sure\tthat the initial RAM filesystem (initramfs) and the booted "
"system behave consistently\tregarding the use of multipathing for all block "
"devices.\tRebuild the initramfs after applying multipath configuration"
"\tchanges."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multipathing is enabled in the system, it also needs to be enabled in the "
"<filename>initramfs</filename> and vice versa. The only exception to this "
"rule is the option <xref linkend=\"vl-multipath-planning-type-noroot-noinitrd"
"\"/> in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-planning-type-noroot\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The multipath configuration must be synchronized between the booted system "
"and the initrd. Therefore, if you change any of the files: <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> , <filename>/etc/multipath/wwids</filename> , "
"<filename>/etc/multipath/bindings</filename> , or other configuration files, "
"or udev rules related to device identification, rebuild initramfs using the "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1402
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dracut -f"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <filename>initrd</filename> and the system are not synchronized, the "
"system will not boot properly and the start-up procedure may result in an "
"emergency shell. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-trouble\"/> for "
"instructions on how to avoid or repair such a scenario."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1410
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling or disabling multipathing in the initramfs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Special care must be taken if the initramfs is rebuilt in non-standard "
"situations, for example, from a rescue system or after booting with the "
"kernel parameter <literal>multipath=off</literal> . <command>dracut</"
"command> will automatically include multipathing support in the initramfs if "
"and only if it detects that the root file system is on a multipath device "
"while the initrd is being built. In such cases, it is necessary to enable or "
"disable multipathing explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable multipath support in the <filename>initrd</filename> , run the "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1424
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dracut --force --add multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable multipath support in <filename>initrd</filename> , run the "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dracut --force --omit multipath"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1431
#, no-c-format
msgid "Persistent device names in the initramfs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tWhen <command>dracut</command> generates the inital RAM disk, it must"
"\trefer to disks and partitions to be mounted in a persistent manner,\tto "
"make sure the system will boot correctly. When\t <command>dracut</command> "
"detects multipath devices, it will use\tthe DM-MP device names such as"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1439
#, no-c-format
msgid "/dev/mapper/3600a098000aad73f00000a3f5a275dc8-part1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tfor this purpose by default.\tThis is good if the system <emphasis>always</"
"emphasis> runs in multipath mode. But if\tthe system is started without "
"multipathing, as described in\t <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-initrd-disable"
"\"/> , booting with such an\tinitramfs will fail, because the\t <filename>/"
"dev/mapper</filename> devices won't exist.\tSee <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"multipath-referring\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> for another possible "
"problem scenario,\tand some background information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tTo prevent this from happening, change <command>dracut</command> 's"
"\tpersistent device naming policy by using the\t <option>--persistent-"
"policy</option> option. It's recommended to set\tuse the <literal>by-uuid</"
"literal> policy:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;dracut --force --omit multipath --persistent-policy=by-uuid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSee also <xref linkend=\"pr-multipath-disable-root\"/> and <xref linkend="
"\"sec-multipath-trouble-ref\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1465
#, no-c-format
msgid "Multipath configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1467
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The built-in <systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> defaults work well for "
"most setups. If customizations are needed, a configuration file needs to be "
"created. The main configuration file is <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> . In addition, files in <filename>/etc/multipath/conf.d/</"
"filename> are taken into account. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-"
"file-precedence\" xrefstyle=\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> for additional information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Vendor recommendations and built-in hardware defaults"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some storage vendors publish recommended values for multipath options in "
"their documentation. These values often represent what the vendor has tested "
"in his environment and found most suitable for the storage product. See the "
"disclaimer in <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-hardware-autodetect\" xrefstyle="
"\"SectTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> has built-in defaults for many "
"storage arrays that are derived from the published vendor recommendations. "
"Run <command>multipath -T</command> to see the current settings for your "
"devices and compare them to vendor recommendations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1496
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is recommended that you create a minimal <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</"
"filename> that just contains those settings you want to change. In many "
"cases, you do not need to create <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> at "
"all."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you prefer working with a configuration template that contains all "
"possible configuration directives, run"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1508
#, no-c-format
msgid "multipath -T &gt;/etc/multipath.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See also <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-best-practice-config\" xrefstyle="
"\"SecTitleOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1516
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>multipath.conf</filename> Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file uses a hierarchy of "
"sections, subsections, and option/value pairs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Whitespace separates tokens. Consecutive whitespace characters are\t "
"collapsed into a single space, unless quoted (see below).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The hash ( <literal>#</literal> )\t and exclamation mark ( <literal>!</"
"literal> ) characters cause the\t rest of the line to be discarded as a "
"comment.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Sections and subsections are started with a section name and an opening "
"brace\t ( <literal>{</literal> ) on the same line, and end with a closing\t "
"brace ( <literal>}</literal> ) on a line on its own.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1543
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Options and values are written on one line. Line continuations\t are "
"unsupported.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1549
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Options and section names must be keywords. The allowed keywords are\t "
"documented in <systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> .\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Values may be enclosed in double quotes ( <literal>\"</literal> ). They\t "
"must be enclosed in quotes if they contain whitespace or comment\t "
"characters. A double quote character inside a value is represented\t by a "
"pair of double quotes ( <literal>\"\"</literal> ).\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t The values of some options are POSIX regular expressions\t (see "
"<systemitem>regex(7)</systemitem> ). They are case sensitive and\t not "
"anchored, so &ldquo; <literal>bar</literal> &rdquo; matches\t &ldquo; "
"<literal>rhabarber</literal> &rdquo;, but not &ldquo;Barbie&rdquo;.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1571
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following example illustrates the syntax:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"section {\n"
"    subsection {\n"
"        option1 value\n"
"        option2      \"complex value!\"\n"
"        option3    \"value with \"\"quoted\"\" word\"\n"
"    } ! subsection end\n"
"} # section end\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1584
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additional configuration files and precedence rules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tAfter <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> ,\tthe tools read files "
"matching the pattern\t <filename>/etc/multipath.conf.d/*.conf</filename> ."
"\tThe additional files follow the same syntax rules as\t <filename>/etc/"
"multipath.conf</filename> . Sections and options can\toccur multiple times. "
"If <emphasis>the same option in the same\tsection</emphasis> \tis set in "
"multiple files,\tor on multiple lines in the same file, the last value takes "
"precedence.\tSeparate precedence rules apply between\t <filename>multipath."
"conf</filename> sections, see below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1601
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>multipath.conf</filename> sections"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <filename>/etc/multipath.conf</filename> file is organized into the "
"following sections. Some options can occur in more than one section. See "
"<systemitem>multipath.conf(5)</systemitem> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1609
#, no-c-format
msgid "defaults"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1611
#, no-c-format
msgid "General default settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:1615
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overriding built-in device properties"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Built-in hardware-specific device properties take precendence over the "
"settings in the <literal>defaults</literal> section. Changes must therefore "
"be made in the <literal>devices</literal> section or in the "
"<literal>overrides</literal> section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1627
#, no-c-format
msgid "blacklist"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1629
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lists devices to ignore. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" "
"xrefstyle=\"HeadingOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1636
#, no-c-format
msgid "blacklist_exceptions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1638
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lists devices to be multipathed even though they are matched by the "
"blacklist. See <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-blacklist\" xrefstyle="
"\"HeadingOnPage\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: storage_multipath.xml:1646
#, no-c-format
msgid "devices"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1648
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\tSettings specific to the storage controller. This section is\ta collection "
"of <literal>device</literal> subsections. Values in this section\toverride "
"values for the same options in the\t <filename>defaults</filename> section, "
"and the built-in settings\tof <systemitem>multipath-tools</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:1655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t <literal>device</literal> entries in the <literal>devices</literal> "
"\tsection are matched against\tthe vendor and product of a device\tusing "
"regular expressions. These entries will be &ldquo;merged&rdquo;,\tsetting "
"all options from matching sections for the device.\tIf the same option is "
"set in multiple matching\t <literal>device</literal> sections, the last "
"device entry\ttakes precedence, even if it is less &ldquo;specific&rdquo; "
"than\tpreceding entries.\tThis applies also if the matching entries appear in"
"\tdifferent configuration files (see <xref linkend=\"sec-multipath-conf-file-"
"precedence\"/> ).\tIn the following example, a device <literal>SOMECORP"
"\tSTORAGE</literal> will use <literal>fast_io_fail_tmo 15</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:1670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"devices {\n"
"    device {\n"
"        vendor SOMECORP\n"
"        product STOR\n"
"        fast_io_fail_tmo 10\n"
"    }\n"
"    device {\n"
"        vendor SOMECORP\n"
"        product .*\n"
"        fast_io_fail_tmo 15\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

