#. Tag: title
#: storage_multipath.xml:3733
#, no-c-format
msgid "Steps for analyzing the situation in emergency mode"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3735
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Try to figure out what failed, by examining failed systemd units and\t "
"the journal.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:3739
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;systemctl --failed\n"
"&prompt.root;journalctl -b -o short-monotonic"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3741
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When looking at the journal, determine the\t <emphasis>first</emphasis> "
"failed unit. When you have found the first\t failure, examine the messages "
"before and around that point in time very\t carefully. Are there any "
"warnings or other suspicious messages?\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3746
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Watch out for the root\t switch (\" <literal>Switching root.</literal> "
"\") and for messages about\t SCSI devices, device-mapper, multipath, and "
"LVM2. Look for\t <command>systemd</command> messages about devices and file "
"systems\t (\" <literal>Found device</literal> …\", \" <literal>Mounting</"
"literal> …\",\t \" <literal>Mounted</literal> …\").\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t Examine the existing devices, both low-level devices and device\t mapper "
"devices (note that some of the commands below may not\t be available in the "
"initramfs):\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:3761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;cat /proc/partitions\n"
"&prompt.root;ls -l /sys/class/block\n"
"&prompt.root;ls -l /dev/disk/by-id/* /dev/mapper/*\n"
"&prompt.root;dmsetup ls --tree\n"
"&prompt.root;lsblk\n"
"&prompt.root;lsscsi\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3768
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t From the output of the commands above, you should get an idea whether the"
"\t low-level devices were successfully probed, and whether or not any\t "
"multipath maps and multipath partitions were set up.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t If the device mapper multipath setup is not as you expect, examine\t the "
"udev properties, in particular <literal>SYSTEMD_READY</literal> \t (see "
"above)\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: storage_multipath.xml:3780
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;udevadm info -e"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_multipath.xml:3783
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t If the previous step showed unexpected udev properties, something\t may "
